<p><strong>Privacy Policy</strong></p>
<p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> June 19, 2026</p>

<hr>

<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
<p>
TTS Voice Bot may process limited information required to provide its services, including Discord User IDs, Server IDs, Channel IDs, Role IDs, and bot configuration settings.
</p>

<h2>2. How Information Is Used</h2>
<ul>
<li>Provide text-to-speech functionality.</li>
<li>Process bot commands.</li>
<li>Store server-specific settings.</li>
<li>Improve reliability, performance, and security.</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Data Storage</h2>
<p>
Only the information necessary for the operation of the bot is stored. Message content is not permanently stored unless required for a specific feature.
</p>

<h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
<p>
TTS Voice Bot does not sell, rent, or share user information with third parties except when required by applicable law.
</p>

<h2>5. Data Security</h2>
<p>
Reasonable technical and organizational measures are implemented to protect stored information against unauthorized access or disclosure.
</p>

<h2>6. User Rights</h2>
<p>
Users may request the deletion of stored bot-related data by contacting the bot's support team.
</p>

<h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
<p>
This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Continued use of the bot after updates constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
</p>

<h2>8. Contact</h2>
<p>
For privacy-related questions or requests, please contact the official TTS Voice Bot support server.
</p>

